The paper addresses the problem of model compression in computer vision, which suggests that it is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category. The paper also proposes a new knowledge distillation method, which falls under the machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. The use of adaptive instance normalization in the proposed method suggests that it may also belong to the neural and evolutionary computing (cs.NE) sub-category. Finally, the paper evaluates the proposed method on different datasets, which suggests that it may also belong to the multimedia (cs.MM) sub-category.
